entries.do_not_edit: The English version of this file (talus_nashal_smuggler.stf) is automatically generated by the SwgConversationEditor.
entries.s_10: I thought so. I don't agree with what our leader is doing to the Selonians. I think we can make a fine profit without having to exploit them.
entries.s_12: I am looking for some Selonian prisoners, maybe you could help me?
entries.s_14: Sure, you can check the cargo manifest database for their storage location. Here, use this password to gain access to the database.
entries.s_15: Get out of here! I've told you all I know.
entries.s_16: I'll leave when I get the codes to that shuttle.
entries.s_20: That's not all. I know there is a traitor in the Selonian den. It's how our leader manipulates the Selonians. Tell the den mother that the Askura deal was fake. She will know what to do.
entries.s_22: I don't know what that means.
entries.s_24: Just tell the den mother. She will know what it means.
entries.s_26: Are you going to be ok here?
entries.s_28: No, which is why I'll be taking off at the first opportunity. The shuttle sitting on the landing pad will make an excellent ticket to a new life.
entries.s_30: You better leave. The guards around here shoot first and never ask questions.
entries.s_6: You're helping those Selonians, aren't you?
